A family was injured and two children ejected after a boat collided with a submerged tree stump on the Vaal river on Thursday. Netcare911 spokesperson Shawn Herbst said paramedics responded to the   accident just before 7.30am. He said four people sustained moderate to serious injuries. “Two of the patients were treated on scene and taken by  ambulance to hospital. “The seriously injured patients were flown by Netcare911 helicopter to a specialist facility,” he said. TimesLIVE